@Franky Frost @***** Here it is: https://www.dropbox.com/sh/1ah4cxnqudwstjq/AAAC1TGlird_aPeW7M-svxT6a?dl=0

I uploaded everything the torrent included, so there may be some weird stuff in there (I even found some strange ragnarok online audio story, lol?). Ragnarok Online's soundtrack is the second/sixth folder in the "01. Official" folder. Ragnarok online II's soundtrack is the second folder in the "05. Other" folder. Sadly, the version of "Swamper" that was included in the download is completely different than the one shown in this video, but every other song seems to be the exact same. I don't know why this is, but it's really unfortunate because I really like this song. I'm new to dropbox, so i don't know if this link will work or not/how long it will last.

snippet.textDisplay: I haven't played MMORPGs or any MMOs all that much, but it's obvious I have developed some kind of affection to ambient game music. I feel enthusiastic, even thrilled listening to this piece even though I've never played Ragnarock Online or anything the like. Despite player chats and other things breaking the illusion a little, the feeling of exploration and amazement is very hard to sweep away.

Thanks again for opening my ears to something new!
